Creating a book is complicated and layered. It’s an adventure, it demands organization, it requires time. Yet, the only way it thrives is from creativity and passion. Call it Home is all of those things. It’s the brilliant designs of @amberinteriors, the stunning documentation of @shadedeggesphotography, the meticulous arranging of @kmek27 — and it was my ultimate honor and joy to pen the words with Amber that tell the story of this adventure. 

Since Made for Living hit shelves in October 2020, we jumped straight into creating our second book, Call it Home. We spent 2021 on the road in homes and parts of the country that I had only dreamed of. The bond we formed, the way we laughed, the beauty we saw, the exhaustion we fought through, and of course the many martinis and bottles of wine that got us through… are all part of this book to us. 

Anyway, just wait until the book actually comes out on October 17th and I’ll write something emotional again then. For now, pre-orders are available, and they mean a whole lot to us. So if you can, order a copy and you’ll make our world go round :) 

The biggest thanks and all my gratitude to @amberinteriors for bringing me on this wild wild ride! And of course @angelinborsics and @nicoletourtelot for being our guiding lights!

Hi! I’m @catchenny, founder of @dulanwine. It’s been years in the making and I couldn’t be happier to finally get these wines poured into your glasses. I’ll share an ‘official intro’ soon, but I’ll keep it short and sweet for now and simply say: Welcome to @dulanwine. I am so honored you are here :)

Stopped by our vineyard this week to pick fresh grass for tonight’s @dulanwine dinner table setting with @cuyana 🌾

WHAT a week! One week of @dulanwine and wow. There is so much to do, so much to learn, and so much opportunity for growth. I am a woman of many words, but I’ll keep it short-ish. Let me start by saying thank you, from the bottom of my heart, to everyone who has welcomed Dulan into the world with me. More to come here, but THANK YOU.

Here are a few moments from the first @dulanwine dinner with @cuyana. A night surrounded by women I admire and eager to learn from. A main theme from our dinner conversation (and a theme I’m working on applying to my life) is to strip ego and ask the questions. It’s ok to not have the answers to everything. It’s ok to ask. Stepping into entrepreneurship is a new frontier and the spirit of it all is learning and being challenged along the way. 

The biggest thank you to @cuyana for making this night possible. @shilparshah is the definition of leading by example and I’m so grateful for your mentorship. 

Photos by the talented @pheebshono. Meal by the delicious @sophies__table.

What a group of women ❤️‍🔥

‘Call it Home’ by @amberinteriors, co-written by me (!!), photographed by @shadedeggesphotography is out tomorrow :)

It was my absolute greatest honor and joy to co-write ‘Call It Home’ with @amberinteriors. Just when I thought co-writing ‘Made for Living’ was a major career moment and the only book I’d work on, Amber brought me on for a second book. Creating ‘Call it Home’ was the ultimate adventure, one that I will never forget. A second book is so much more creatively challenging than the first. And holding this in my hands has never felt so fulfilling. 

We poured our hearts into creating this book. Every word written, every photo taken. It’s not easy translating years of Amber’s design work into a book, but I must say… the final product is something we are all so proud of. 

Tomorrow is the official publication date, but we have been ready for you all to see this since we started creating this book in 2021. Fall 2023 felt so very far away, and here we are two and a half years later. Call it Home is published :) 

What a crew, what a ride! Thank you for being the best in the biz and for bringing me along on this wild journey @amberinteriors. To the entire team that made this book possible, you are one of a kind. I feel so lucky to have worked alongside you @shadedeggesphotography @angelinladams @nicoletourtelot @kmek27 @briyana_warden @morgan.wallach_ and the entire Amber Interiors design team ♥️

2023 Harvest ✔️✔️

this 30 second video doesn’t show the multiple 6+ hour harvests on our steep hills, rugged terrain, tractor malfunctions, etc etc… harvest is incredibly laborious. the attention to detail, the logistics, all while nature’s unpredictability reigns supreme. but that’s what this biz is all about. roll with the punches and work damn hard while you’re doin it! (it definitely ain’t cute!) i am proud of this season and excited for what’s to come 🍇
